<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 2836/98 of 22 December 1998 on integrating of gender issues in development cooperation </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2836/98 soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse k&uuml;simuste arengukoost&ouml;&ouml;sse integreerimise kohta </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> 22. detsember 1998 EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 130w thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 130w, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure referred to in Article 189c of the Treaty (2), </inglise>
<eesti> tegutsedes asutamislepingu artiklis 189c nimetatud korras ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas the importance of women's economic and social roles in developing countries has led to increasing international recognition that their full participation without discrimination is indispensable for sustainable and effective development; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) naiste majandusliku ja sotsiaalse asendi t&auml;htsus arengumaades on kaasa toonud kasvava rahvusvahelise m&otilde;istmise, et nende t&auml;ielik, diskrimineerimiseta osalemine on h&auml;davajalik s&auml;&auml;stvaks ja t&otilde;husaks arenguks; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas their contribution to development is presently achieved in the face of formidable obstacles specific to women, limiting the outcome of their work and reducing the benefits to society as a whole; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) naiste panus arengusse on praegu saavutatud hoolimata tohututest naiste ette seatud takistustest, mis piiravad nende t&ouml;&ouml; tulemuslikkust ja v&auml;hendavad kogu &uuml;hiskonna saadavat kasu; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas these obstacles include persistent and severe disparities between women and men in the right to equal participation in development for women, access to basic services, particularly in the areas of education, training and health, access to decision-making and control over economic resources; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) nende takistuste hulka kuulub endiselt selge ebav&otilde;rdsus naiste ja meeste vahel naiste v&otilde;rdses &otilde;iguses osaleda arengus, p&otilde;hiteenuste k&auml;ttesaadavuses, eelk&otilde;ige hariduse, koolituse ja tervise alal, otsuste tegemises ja majandusressursside haldamises; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas development interventions have frequently failed to address adequately the differences between women's and men's situations, roles, opportunities and priorities, thereby reducing their overall success; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) arengumeetmed pole sageli suutnud piisavalt k&auml;sitleda naiste ja meeste asendi, rollide, v&otilde;imaluste ja prioriteetide erinevusi, v&auml;hendades seega nende &uuml;ldist edu; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas redressing gender disparities and enhancing the role of women are crucial for social justice and the effectiveness of development efforts; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) soolise ebav&otilde;rdsuse heastamine ja naiste osa v&auml;&auml;rtustamine on otsustavad &uuml;hiskondliku &otilde;igluse ja arengupingutuste t&otilde;hususe seisukohalt; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas development cooperation must encourage the necessary accompanying changes in attitudes, structures and mechanisms at political, economic, legal, community and household level; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) arengukoost&ouml;&ouml; peab edendama vajalikke kaasnevaid muutusi suhtumises, struktuurides ja mehhanismides poliitilisel, majanduslikul, &otilde;iguslikul, &uuml;hiskondlikul ja perekondlikul tasandil; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas it is now recognized that though specific efforts to enhance the role of women in development remain as necessary as ever, the focus must widen to encompass both men's and women's roles, responsibilities, needs, access to resources and decision-making, and the inter-relationship between them, known as gender issues; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) n&uuml;&uuml;d tunnistatakse, et kuigi konkreetsed pingutused naiste osa tugevdamiseks arengus on endiselt vajalikud, peavad huvid laienema, h&otilde;lmates nii meeste kui naiste rolle, kohustusi, vajadusi, varade kasutusv&otilde;imalusi ja otsuste tegemist ning nende omavahelisi suhteid, mida tuntakse soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse k&uuml;simustena; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas development effectiveness requires that gender analysis should be systematically integrated into the conception, design, implementation and evaluation of all development interventions and strategies; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) arengu t&otilde;husus n&otilde;uab soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse anal&uuml;&uuml;si s&uuml;stemaatilist liitmist k&otilde;igi arengumeetmete ja -strateegiate loomise, kujundamise, rakendamise ja hindamisega; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas the foregoing analysis is set out in more detail in the Commission's communication to the Council and the European Parliament on integrating gender issues in development cooperation of 18 September 1995 and was endorsed by the Council in its Resolution of 20 December 1995; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) eelnenud anal&uuml;&uuml;s on &uuml;ksikasjalikumalt esitatud komisjoni 18. septembri 1995. aasta teates n&otilde;ukogule ja Euroopa Parlamendile soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse k&uuml;simuste arengukoost&ouml;&ouml;sse integreerimise kohta ja seda on kinnitanud n&otilde;ukogu oma 20. detsembri 1995. aasta otsusega; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Whereas in a series of conclusions from 1982 to 1993 the Council has stressed the importance it attaches to women's role in development; </inglise>
<eesti> 10) reas 1982.-1993. aasta otsustes on n&otilde;ukogu r&otilde;hutanud, et ta peab naiste osa arengus t&auml;htsaks; </eesti>
<inglise> (11) Whereas the Community and its Member States were signatories to the Nairobi Forward-Looking Strategies in 1985 and to the Declaration and Platform for Action of the Fourth World Conference on Women at Beijing in 1995, which stressed the need for action against worldwide obstacles to gender equality and to ensure that this perspective is reflected in all policies and programmes; </inglise>
<eesti> 11) &uuml;hendus ja selle liikmesriigid on kirjutanud alla Nairobi tulevikustrateegiale aastal 1985 ning Pekingis aastal 1995 peetud neljanda naiste maailmakonverentsi deklaratsioonile ja tegevusprogrammile, mis r&otilde;hutavad vajadust v&otilde;tta meetmeid sugupoolte v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse &uuml;lemaailmsete takistuste vastu ning tagada selle vaatepunkti kajastumine igas poliitikas ja programmis; </eesti>
<inglise> (12) Whereas the United Nations Convention on the Elimination of all forms of Discrimination against Women (1979) considers discrimination against women as an obstacle to development which parties agree to eliminate using all appropriate means, and the UN Declaration on the Right to Development (1986) emphasizes the right of all persons to participate in and contribute to development and the need to undertake effective measures to ensure that women have an active role in the development process; </inglise>
<eesti> 12) &Uuml;hinenud Rahvaste Organisatsiooni konventsioon naiste diskrimineerimise k&otilde;igi vormide likvideerimise kohta (1979) k&auml;sitleb naiste diskrimineerimist arengu takistusena, mille konventsiooniosalised n&otilde;ustuvad k&otilde;iki asjakohaseid meetmeid kasutades k&otilde;rvaldama, ja &Uuml;RO arengu&otilde;iguse deklaratsioon (1986) r&otilde;hutab k&otilde;igi isikute &otilde;igust osaleda arengus ja anda sellesse oma panus ning vajadust v&otilde;tta t&otilde;husaid meetmeid, et tagada naiste aktiivne roll arengus; </eesti>
<inglise> (13) Whereas the European Parliament has emphasized in numerous Resolutions, and particularly in its Resolution of 14 May 1992 on the situation of women in developing countries and its Resolution of 15 June 1995 on the fourth World Conference on Women in Beijing, the need to integrate proper attention to women's roles and priorities in Community development cooperation and to take adequate measures to ensure active implementation of the conclusions of the Beijing Conference; </inglise>
<eesti> 13) Euroopa Parlament on mitmes otsuses, eriti 14. mai 1992. aasta otsuses naiste olukorra kohta arengumaades ja 15. juuni 1995. aasta otsuses neljanda naiste maailmakonverentsi kohta Pekingis, r&otilde;hutanud vajadust p&ouml;&ouml;rata &uuml;henduse arengukoost&ouml;&ouml;s asjakohast t&auml;helepanu naiste rollile ja prioriteetidele ning v&otilde;tta piisavad meetmed Pekingi konverentsi otsuste aktiivse rakendamise tagamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (14) Whereas the Resolution of the Council and the Representatives of the Governments of the Member States of 20 December 1995 endorses the Commission's communication on the same subject, requires the full integration of gender issues in development cooperation and coordination between the Commission and Member States in this field, and sets out guidelines which also translate into the field of development cooperation the political commitments undertaken at Beijing; </inglise>
<eesti> 14) n&otilde;ukogu ja liikmesriikide valitsuste esindajate 20. detsembri 1995. aasta otsus kinnitab komisjoni samateemalist teatist, n&otilde;uab soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse k&uuml;simuste t&auml;ielikku integreerimist arengukoost&ouml;&ouml;sse ning komisjoni ja liikmesriikide tegevuse koosk&otilde;lastamist sellel alal ja esitab juhised, mis toovad Pekingis v&otilde;etud poliitilised kohustused ka arengukoost&ouml;&ouml;sse; </eesti>
<inglise> (15) Whereas this approach is further endorsed by the Resolution of the Council and the Member States on human and social development of 22 November 1996; </inglise>
<eesti> 15) seda l&auml;henemisviisi kinnitab veelgi n&otilde;ukogu ja liikmesriikide 22. novembri 1996. aasta resolutsioon inim- ja &uuml;hiskondliku arengu kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (16) Whereas the recognized importance of these issues to development effectiveness makes it appropriate to envisage specific activities aimed at ensuring adequate attention to gender issues across the mainstream of Community financial instruments, which should increasingly assume responsibility for these key questions; </inglise>
<eesti> 16) et neid k&uuml;simusi peetakse arengu t&otilde;hususe seisukohalt t&auml;htsaks, on p&otilde;hjendatud konkreetsed meetmed, mis on suunatud soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse k&uuml;simustele k&uuml;llaldase t&auml;helepanu p&ouml;&ouml;ramisele &uuml;henduse p&otilde;hiliste rahastamisvahendite kaudu, mille abil tuleks v&otilde;tta &uuml;ha suurem vastutus nende v&otilde;tmek&uuml;simuste eest; </eesti>
<inglise> (17) Whereas the most effective approach is strategic and precisely targeted sensitization initiatives capable of achieving a substantial multiplier effect, rather than the funding of small-scale operational projects; whereas Community development cooperation aid should also be used to a greater extent for specific action in favour of women; </inglise>
<eesti> 17) k&otilde;ige t&otilde;husamaks l&auml;henemisviisiks on strateegilised ja t&auml;pselt suunatud teadlikustamisalgatused, mille abil v&otilde;ib saavutada m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rset mitmekordset m&otilde;ju, mitte aga v&auml;ikesemahuliste tegevuskavade rahastamine; &uuml;henduse arengukoost&ouml;&ouml;abi tuleks samuti ulatuslikumalt kasutada konkreetseteks meetmeteks naiste kasuks; </eesti>
<inglise> (18) Whereas the importance of Community activities in the field of development cooperation necessitates measures by the Community to ensure its implementation of its commitments at Beijing, complementary to those undertaken by Member States; </inglise>
<eesti> 18) &uuml;henduse meetmete t&auml;htsus arengukoost&ouml;&ouml;s n&otilde;uab &uuml;henduse meetmeid, mis tagaksid Pekingi kohustuste rakendamise lisaks liikmesriikide v&otilde;etud kohustustele; </eesti>
<inglise> (19) Whereas measures need to be taken to finance the activities covered by this Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> 19) tuleb v&otilde;tta meetmeid k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega h&otilde;lmatud tegevuse rahastamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (20) Whereas a financial reference amount, within the meaning of point 2 of the Declaration by the European Parliament, the Council and the Commission of 6 March 1995 on the incorporation of financial provisions into legislative acts (3) is included in this Regulation for the period 1999 to 2003, without thereby affecting the powers of the budgetary authority as they are defined by the Treaty; </inglise>
<eesti> 20) k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses sisaldub rahanduss&auml;tete inkorporeerimist seadusandlikesse aktidesse k&auml;sitleva Euroopa Parlamendi, n&otilde;ukogu ja komisjoni 6. m&auml;rtsi 1995. aasta deklaratsiooni punktile 2 vastav l&auml;htesumma aastateks 1999-2003, mis ei m&otilde;juta asutamislepingus m&auml;&auml;ratletud eelarvep&auml;devate institutsioonide volitusi; </eesti>
<inglise> (21) Whereas detailed rules for implementation, and in particular the form of action, the recipients of the aid and the decision-making procedures should be laid down, </inglise>
<eesti> 21) tuleks s&auml;testada &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad, eriti tegevusvorm, abi saajad ja otsustamismenetlus, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The Community shall provide financial assistance and technical expertise to support the mainstreaming of the gender perspective into all its development cooperation policies and interventions. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendus annab rahalist abi ja tehnilisi teadmisi soolise aspekti s&uuml;valaiendamiseks iga oma arengukoost&ouml;&ouml;poliitika ja meetme puhul. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The assistance provided pursuant to this Regulation shall complement, reinforce and coordinate assistance provided pursuant to other instruments of development cooperation, including those existing at intergovernmental and/or national level, with a view to taking fully into account gender considerations in Community policies and interventions. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt antud abi t&auml;iendab, tugevdab ja koosk&otilde;lastab vastavalt muudele, sealhulgas valitsustevahelisel ja/v&otilde;i siseriiklikul tasandil arengukoost&ouml;&ouml; vahenditele antud abi, pidades silmas sooliste l&auml;htekohtade t&auml;ielikku arvestamist &uuml;henduse poliitikas ja meetmetes. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Regulation'gender issues' means the different and interrelated roles, responsibilities and opportunities of women and men relative to development, which are culturally specific and socially constructed, and can change over time, inter alia, as a result of policy interventions. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses t&auml;hendavad "soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse k&uuml;simused" naiste ja meeste erinevaid ja omavahel seotud rolle, mida seostatakse arenguga, kohustusi ja v&otilde;imalusi, mis on kultuuri- ja &uuml;hiskonnaomased ning v&otilde;ivad aja jooksul muu hulgas poliitiliste meetmete tulemusena muutuda. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The following are the central objectives of activities to be carried out pursuant to this Regulation: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaste meetmete kesksed eesm&auml;rgid on j&auml;rgmised: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) to support the mainstreaming of gender analysis in all areas of development cooperation, taking particular account of the legal and actual status of women and men, their needs and their contribution to society and the family; to support the adoption of a gender-sensitive approach in the conception, design and implementation of Community development policies and interventions at macro, meso and micro level, as well as in their monitoring and evaluation; </inglise>
<eesti> a) toetada soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse s&uuml;valaiendamist k&otilde;igis arengukoost&ouml;&ouml; valdkondades, v&otilde;ttes eriti arvesse naiste ja meeste &otilde;iguslikku ja tegelikku seisundit, nende vajadusi ja nende panust &uuml;hiskonda ja pereellu; toetada sootundliku l&auml;henemise kasutuselev&otilde;tmist &uuml;henduse arengupoliitika ja meetmete v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamisel, kujundamisel ja rakendamisel k&otilde;rg-, kesk- ja alamtasandil, samuti nende j&auml;relevalves ja hindamisel; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) to support and facilitate the inclusion of actions addressing major gender disparities and on an appropriately large scale, particularly with regard to access to resources, services and participation in the decision-making processes in political, economic and social life, in the mainstream of Community development interventions; </inglise>
<eesti> b) toetada ja h&otilde;lbustada olulist soolist ebav&otilde;rdsust k&auml;sitlevate meetmete h&otilde;lmamist k&otilde;igisse &uuml;henduse arengumeetmetesse piisavas ulatuses, pidades eriti silmas varade ja teenuste k&auml;ttesaadavust ja poliitilise, majandusliku ja &uuml;hiskondliku elu otsuste tegemises osalemist; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) to lead progressively to a situation in 2003 where a substantially increased percentage of Community interventions satisfy the OECD/DAC criteria for gender integration or positive action; </inglise>
<eesti> c) j&otilde;uda aastaks 2003 j&auml;rk-j&auml;rgult olukorrani, et m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt suur osa &uuml;henduse meetmeid vastaks OECD arenguabikomitee (DAC) seatud kriteeriumidele soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse k&uuml;simuste h&otilde;lmamise v&otilde;i positiivsete meetmete kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) to develop and promote endogenous public and private capacities in developing countries which can take the responsibility and initiative for mainstreaming the gender dimension in the development effort. </inglise>
<eesti> d) arendada ja edendada arengumaades kohalikke riiklikke ja eraressursse, mis suudavad v&otilde;tta vastutuse ja algatuse soolise m&otilde;&otilde;tme s&uuml;valaiendamiseks riigi arengus. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Activities eligible for financing include, in particular: </inglise>
<eesti> Rahastamistingimustele vastavad eelk&otilde;ige j&auml;rgmised meetmed: </eesti>
<inglise> - provision of technical advice and support on the integration of gender issues in development interventions; </inglise>
<eesti> - tehniliste n&otilde;uannete ja toetuse andmine soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse k&uuml;simuste integreerimisel arengumeetmetesse; </eesti>
<inglise> - activities aimed at including gender implications in analyses, policies, country and sector strategies; </inglise>
<eesti> - meetmed, mille eesm&auml;rk on soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse m&otilde;ju kaasamine anal&uuml;&uuml;sidesse, poliitikasse, riigi ja sektoristrateegiatesse; </eesti>
<inglise> - schemes to build up the institutional and operational capacities of developing countries on gender issues at national, regional and local level, including, as regards legislative and administrative action, on equal rights for men and women; </inglise>
<eesti> - kavad arengumaades institutsiooniliste ja toimivate v&otilde;imaluste rajamiseks riiklikul, piirkondlikul ja kohalikul tasandil, h&otilde;lmates naiste ja meeste v&otilde;rdseid &otilde;igusi seadusandlikus ja haldustegevuses; </eesti>
<inglise> - supporting the collection and dissemination of data desegregated by sex; </inglise>
<eesti> - sugupoolte j&auml;rgi liigitatud andmete kogumise ja levitamise toetamine; </eesti>
<inglise> - development of methodologies, guidelines, manuals, procedures, indicators and other operational instruments seeking to improve the integration of gender issues in development activities; </inglise>
<eesti> - meetodite, juhiste, k&auml;siraamatute, korralduste, n&auml;itajate ja muude t&ouml;&ouml;vahendite v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamine, millega p&uuml;&uuml;takse parandada soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse k&uuml;simuste integreerimist arengumeetmetesse; </eesti>
<inglise> - thematic monitoring and evaluations; </inglise>
<eesti> - temaatiline j&auml;relevalve ja hinnangud; </eesti>
<inglise> - training and sensitization of key decision-makers in the Commission and the developing countries; </inglise>
<eesti> - komisjoni ja arengumaade kesksete otsustajate koolitamine ja teadlikkuse suurendamine; </eesti>
<inglise> - support to the formulation, follow-up and monitoring of national plans in developing countries designed to implement the Platform for Action of the Beijing Conference; </inglise>
<eesti> - Pekingi konverentsi tegevusprogrammi rakendamiseks kavandatud arengumaade riiklike kavade koostamise, kontrolli ja j&auml;relevalve toetamine; </eesti>
<inglise> - actions within the framework of coordination with Member States on integrating gender issues in development cooperation. </inglise>
<eesti> - liikmesriikidega koosk&otilde;lastatud meetmed soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse k&uuml;simuste integreerimiseks arengukoost&ouml;&ouml;sse. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Particular attention will be given to incorporating gender issues into emerging areas of development cooperation. </inglise>
<eesti> Erilist t&auml;helepanu p&ouml;&ouml;ratakse soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse k&uuml;simuste integreerimisele arengukoost&ouml;&ouml; uutesse valdkondadesse. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Beneficiaries of activities carried out under this Regulation may include public authorities and government agencies, decentralized departments, regional bodies, universities and research centres, traditional and local communities, trade unions, non-governmental organizations, public utility associations and associations representing local people, particularly women, as well as cooperatives and agricultural and craft-based credit institutions. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt v&otilde;etud meetmetest v&otilde;ivad kasu saada ametiv&otilde;imud ja valitsusasutused, detsentraliseeritud asutused, regionaalorganid, &uuml;likoolid ja uurimiskeskused, traditsioonilised ja kohalikud kogukonnad, ameti&uuml;hingud, valitsusv&auml;lised organisatsioonid, stipendiumifondid ja kohalikke inimesi, eelk&otilde;ige naisi esindavad &uuml;hingud, samuti &uuml;hendused ning p&otilde;llumajanduse ja k&auml;sit&ouml;&ouml;nduse krediidiasutused. </eesti>
<inglise> Priority will be given to endogenous structures that can play a role in developing local capacities with respect to gender. </inglise>
<eesti> Eelis&otilde;igus antakse kohalikele struktuuridele, mis suudavad osaleda kohalikus soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse v&otilde;imaluste arendamises. </eesti>
